<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-073-378  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 073 378.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Jan 20 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Three indicted for stealing classified data. (Kevin L. Poulsen,Robert Gilligan, Mark Lottor)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Woods, Wendy.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer industryCourt CasesInvestigationsTheft of InformationComputer hackersLegal Issues.andO;Person:    Poulsen, Kevin L. (cases); Gilligan, Robert (cases); Lottor, Mark(cases).andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>THREE INDICTED FOR STEALING CLASSIFIED DATA SAN JOSE, CALIFORNIA, U.S.A.,andO;1990 JAN 18 (NB) -- Authorities say this may be the most disturbing hackingincident ever.andP;  They say hackers have not only penetrated what was supposedto be a secure military computer, but have manipulated California's PacificBell phone system.andM;Kevin L. Poulsen, 24, Robert Gilligan, 31, and Mark Lottor, 25, have beenindicted by a federal grand jury in San Jose on 19 counts.andP;  The trio isaccused of a variety of break-ins, the most serious of which, authoritiessay, occurred in the U.S.andP;  Army's MASNET computer network.andP;  There, sometimein late 1987 or early 1988, classified information on &quot;air tasking orders&quot;for a month-long military exercise was obtained.andP;  The exercise was slated forNorth Carolina.andM;The government alleges that the three men were not only exploring classifieddata on military computers, but they also managed to obtain unlisted phonenumbers for the Soviet Consulate in San Francisco via illegal means.andP;  Inaddition, they are said to have diverted Pacific Bell and governmentcomputers for their own use, including for purposes of wiretap.andP;  Theindictment cites incidents in which phone company facilities were burglarizedand badges, directories, and test equipment were stolen.andM;The charges also list a wiretap on the line of a North Hollywood woman, whois said to have been Poulsen's girlfriend.andM;Authorities are not speculating on a motive at this time, but say thePoulsen, for one, has a history of hacking incidents dating back to histeens.andM;While Poulsen remains at large and is believe to be in Los Angeles somewhere,the other two men named in the indictment are expected to surrendervoluntarily to authorities.andM;(Wendy Woods/19900120)</TEXT></DOC>